- When Deadly_Nightshade dips below 0.75 and arsenic dips below 0.49, whilst at the same time, cyanide dips below 0.32 or Nerve_Gas goes above 0.75, decrease methylene by 0.05
	- If sarin dips below 0.64 and snakeVenom dips below 0.42, whilst at the same time, insecticide dips below 0.5 or formaldehyde dips below 0.36, try increasing methylene by 0.01
	- If Deadly_Nightshade dips below 0.28 or sarin dips below 0.26, whilst at the same time, arsenic goes above 0.27 or cyanide dips below 0.32, reduce insulin by 0.04
	- When either formaldehyde dips below 0.29, Nerve_Gas goes above 0.65, or perhaps snakeVenom dips below 0.33, increment insulin by 0.03
	- If formaldehyde dips below 0.68 and Nerve_Gas dips below 0.52, or on the other hand, snakeVenom dips below 0.36, decrement protamine by 0.03
	- When insecticide dips below 0.25 and Deadly_Nightshade dips below 0.43, whilst at the same time, sarin goes above 0.46 or arsenic goes above 0.67, increase protamine by 0.05
	- If sarin goes above 0.55 or arsenic dips below 0.66, whilst at the same time, snakeVenom dips below 0.36 or Nerve_Gas dips below 0.42, decrement charcoal by 0.01
	- If cyanide goes above 0.58 and insecticide goes above 0.36, or on the other hand, formaldehyde goes above 0.4 and Deadly_Nightshade goes above 0.48, raise charcoal by 0.05
	- If formaldehyde goes above 0.66 and Deadly_Nightshade goes above 0.51, or on the other hand, Nerve_Gas dips below 0.42 and insecticide goes above 0.48, try decreasing glucagon by 0.03
	- If snakeVenom dips below 0.73 or cyanide dips below 0.57, or on the other hand, arsenic dips below 0.38 and sarin goes above 0.28, increase glucagon by 0.02


Your conditional statements should:

consider the following poisons:

	- formaldehyde
	- snakeVenom
	- arsenic
	- insecticide
	- sarin
	- cyanide
	- Nerve_Gas
	- Deadly_Nightshade


and modify the following antidotes:

	- methylene
	- insulin
	- protamine
	- charcoal
	- glucagon


- There are many ways to complete this task but you should only use the
following commands:

	if(){}
	+=
	-=

*/

//Declare the poison variables
var formaldehyde;
var snakeVenom;
var arsenic;
var insecticide;
var sarin;
var cyanide;
var Nerve_Gas;
var Deadly_Nightshade;


//Declare the antidote variables
var methylene;
var insulin;
var protamine;
var charcoal;
var glucagon;


//This variable is used for drawing the graph
var graphs;


function setup()
{

	createCanvas(800,600);
	strokeWeight(2);

	//initialise the poisons and antidotes
	formaldehyde = 0.5;
	snakeVenom = 0.5;
	arsenic = 0.5;
	insecticide = 0.5;
	sarin = 0.5;
	cyanide = 0.5;
	Nerve_Gas = 0.5;
	Deadly_Nightshade = 0.5;
	methylene = 0.5;
	insulin = 0.5;
	protamine = 0.5;
	charcoal = 0.5;
	glucagon = 0.5;


	//fills the graph with empty values
	graphs = [];

	for(var i = 0; i < 8; i++)
	{
		graphs.push([]);
		for(var j = 0; j < 512; j++)
		{
			graphs[i].push(0.5);
		}
	}

}